Reasoning: The paper deals with the mathematical concept of affine rigidity, which has applications in point registration and localization. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), Computational Geometry (cs.CG), Scientific Computing (cs.SI), Numerical Analysis (cs.NA), or Graph Theory (cs.GT) sub-categories. The focus on hypergraphs and graphs, as well as the mention of frameworks and rigidity, suggests that cs.CG and cs.GT are the most likely sub-categories. However, the mention of matrix rank and manifold learning suggests that cs.DM, cs.SI, and cs.NA are also possible sub-categories.
